elements.textContent:
How to enroll in a health plan:
Complete the SF-2809, Health Benefits Election Form:
	http://www.opm.gov/forms/pdf_fill/sf2809.pdf

Follow the instructions included with the form.
Print copy 1, Official Personnel Folder copy, and send it to Human Resources Operations in Minneapolis within 60 days of your employment date.  The other copies are not needed. This form may be faxed to 612-336-3545, or mailed.
Even if you elect not to enroll in a health plan at this time, you are required to complete the SF-2809, electing not to enroll, and send it to Human Resources Operations in Minneapolis within 60 days of your employment date.
If you miss this opportunity to enroll, you will need to wait for the annual open season, or a qualifying life event.
